name: DevMemphis - A new Meetup for Memphis Software Developers - Topic: Docker
description:
Topic:
Clone Build Run
One click deployment of multi-project applications with git and docker

Presenter: Daniel Lissner - Senior Software Engineer @ Weigh Up

modern applications typically consist of various clients, backends and services, each with their own codebase and managed in separate projects. In this talk we'll look at using docker, docker-compose, and some features of git and github to make developing, running, deploying and collaborating on complex applications simple.

Come hang out and eat pizza with Memphis developers.

What is devMemphis?
DevMemphis is a general purpose technical user-group for anyone in the Memphis Community interested in programming, software development, security, dev-ops, developer experience and related topics. DevMemphis is free to anyone who wants to attend and meets on the first Tuesday of each month at the FedEx Institute of Technology on the University of Memphis campus
how_to_find_us: We will be upstairs in Rm 225. Limited free parking is available on and around campus. Paid parking is available in the FIT parking garage on Innovation Dr.

name: #memtech Fresh Burger Friday
description:
Join us the first Friday each month for good burgers and good conversation! On Fridays, the Butcher Shop makes some of the best hamburgers in town from fresh steak trimmings. You can see a menu at http://thebutchershop.com/fresh-burger-friday/ .

Come and discuss technology, business, phones, and software with other like-minded technical people. This monthly lunch meetup is informal and has no presentations or set agenda.

Seating goes quickly at Fresh Burger Friday, so please RSVP to ensure we have space for you.
how_to_find_us: When you arrive, get in line and get your burger, fries and whatever else you want, and then come find us. We usually try to grab a table in the back. Look for the "Memtech Fresh Burger Friday" sign.

name: Memphis Game Developers
description:
6pm - Chit chat and eat! Food and drink provided!
7pm - Presentation
-------------------------------------------
Every month we host a game development related workshop at the Fedex Institute of Technology on the main campus of the University of Memphis. March's workshop will cover software development and game design issues instead of actual technology development. Before you spend hours doing working on the code, learn how to save yourself future headaches and problems! Also, you can meet other people in the local game development community!

Parking: There is the Central parking lot as well as a garage right across from FIT (2$ per hour for the garage).

Find us on Discord! https://discord.gg/FukPzQh
Support our meetups on Patreon! https://www.patreon.com/MemphisGameDevs

name: #memtech Coworking day
description:

name: Code Together
description:
Interested in coding with other people or getting help on a project that you're working on?

If you said yes to this, then this might be the event for you!

This Code Together event is a time for you to work alongside and connect with other people in your local community.

Now, it's important to note that this isn't a class, so there won't be a teacher, but it is your opportunity to talk with other people and get help jumpstarting your learning process or with a programming lesson / personal project you've been working on.

Come with your laptop, a notebook & pen, and/or a drive to learn!

1:00PM MEETUP LOCATION:
We'll be meeting and working inside Einstein Bros. Bagels off of Poplar. Just look for a person with a purple Code Connective lanyard. It should be easy to find us!

name: Memphis M365 Users Group Meeting
description:
Join us for the September Memphis M365 User Group meeting! Learn more about M365, network, and share your thoughts, input, and questions.

Topic:

Join us in this March session to understand what Microsoft 365 capabilities are and what's involved in a deployment.
In this session we will break down the overall capability blocks and solution building blocks that cover M365 Enterprise and M365 Business and what that means.

If you plan to attend, please RSVP so we make sure we have plenty of accommodations, and whom to contact if there are any changes that need to be communicated.

We look forward to seeing you at the meeting!
